  "title": "Special Pricing Term and Condition",
  "description": "A Special Pricing Condition is a bank-authorized override of standard product pricing terms that is applied in response to a strategic campaign, regulatory requirement, or major business event. Unlike product-level discount pricing, where profitability is absorbed within the product, a Special Pricing Condition is usually funded through a campaign or compliance budget so that the shortfall does not distort product-level performance.\r\n\r\nSpecial Pricing Conditions may:\r\n\r\n- Temporarily waive or adjust product fees, charges, or interest rates.\r\n- Apply eligibility rules based on campaigns, customer segments, or regulatory directives.\r\n- Include non-product concessions (e.g., vouchers, gifts, service credits).\r\n- Be centrally captured, broadcast, and verified to ensure controlled application across systems.\r\n\r\nA Special Pricing Condition is a time-bound, strategic override of standard product pricing, governed at the bank level, and often linked to campaigns or compliance measures  with costs allocated outside the product P&L.",
